#
# Template for user-defined custom excludes
#
# Usage:
#   1. Copy to /etc/aide/aide.conf.d/99-custom.conf
#   2. Edit with your service-specific excludes
#   3. Test: sudo aide --config-check
#   4. Regenerate DB: sudo aideinit

# Example: Application cache directory
# !/opt/myapp/cache

# Example: Application data directory (monitor structure, not content)
# /opt/myapp/data VarDir

# Example: Application logs (growing files)
# /opt/myapp/logs ActLog

# Example: Application configuration (full monitoring)
# /opt/myapp/config Full

# ============================================
# AIDE Group Quick Reference
# ============================================
#
# Full     = Complete integrity check (immutable files)
# VarFile  = Metadata only (content can change)
# VarDir   = Monitor directory structure
# ActLog   = Active logs (files can grow)
# RotLog   = Rotated logs
# OwnerMode = Only ownership and permissions
#
# See docs/FALSE_POSITIVE_REDUCTION.md for details
